ethod, as well as deconstruction. In order to satisfy the postulate of pluralism in interpretation, the hermeneutical theory draws upon a variety of ancient and modern sources such as Aristotle, T. S. Eliot, Hans Urs von Balthasar, and Paul Ricœur.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aBibel /Interpretation. 4aGenesis. 4aHermeneutik. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBible.  aBiblical Studies.  aHermeneutics.  aInterpretation.  aReligion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2009z9783110219494oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311020974740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020975440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110209754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110209754/original  a978-3-11-021952-4  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009b2009  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_S